                              cases also above it).</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> On some leaves, writing rulings are continued beyond
                              A vertical line, towards the ruling pricks (irregularly; s., e.g.
                                 <locus target="#78r">78r</locus>, 89r).</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> One or two ruled lines have been left empty at the bottom, on <locus from="64v" to="69v">64v-69v</locus>, and at the top, on <locus target="#28r">28r</locus> (space for ornamental band).</ab>

                           <ab type="punctuation" subtype="Executed">not quite regularly;</ab>
                           <ab type="punctuation" subtype="Usage">not always logical.</ab>
                           <ab type="punctuation" subtype="Dividers">
                              <list>
                                 
                                 <item xml:id="div2"> I. Colon. </item>
                                 <item xml:id="div3"> II. Four dot asterisk (used throughout the
                                    text);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div4"> nine dot asterisk (used throughout the
                                    text);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div5"> doubled nine dot asterisks, with lines in
                                    between (esp. fols.: 25ra, l.23; 39va, l.22; 42ra, l.9);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div6"> doubled colon, with lines in between (esp.
                                       <locus target="#38ra">38ra</locus>, l.3).</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div7"> Sentence dividers are accompanied by the
                                    paragraph signs, on the left from the text column and between
                                    the two columns (used throughout the text).</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div8"> III. Nine dot asterisks, connected with lines
                                    (e.g. fols.: 25ra, l.33; 36vb, l.38; 59vb, l.24; 118vb,
                                    l.22);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div9"> chain of black lines and red and black dots
                                    (e.g. fols.: 9vb, l.12; 25ra, <locus target="#18">18</locus>,
                                    23; 35ra, l.1; 41ra, l.7; 96ra, l.1);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div10"> chain of coronis signs, between a chain of
                                    double black lines (filled red in between) and nine dot
                                    asterisks, and a chain of double black lines and four dot
                                    asterisks (esp. <locus target="#37va">37va</locus>b);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div11"> chain of coronis signs, between a chain of
                                    double black lines and nine dot asterisks, and a chain of black
                                    lines and dots (esp. <locus target="#59vb">59vb</locus>);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div12"> Coronis (e.g. fols.: 35ra, l.1; 37vab; 45va,
                                    l.1; 46va, l.14; 79vb, l.22);</item>
                                 <item xml:id="div13"> Crux ansata with coronis, marking the
                                    beginning of each new text (esp. fols.: 25rb, l.1; 100va,
                                    l.15).</item>
                                 <note>- Between Texts I-1 and I-2 the text divider is missing.</note>
                              </list>
                           </ab>
                           <ab type="CruxAnsata"> </ab>
                        </layout>
