                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1450" notAfter="1500">Second half of the 15th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; 
 three or five lines in the
                           incipit page of each text, alternating with black lines (in one or both
                           columns); sometimes the first line of the account proper;
 Ethiopic
                           numerals (e.g., fol. 26va, l.15) or their elements;
 elements of the
                           punctuation signs and of the crux ansata.</seg>
                        <note>- Compressed script used on <locus target="#36vb">36vb</locus>.</note>
                        
                     
                     <note>The handwriting is characterized by
                        uniform, rounded, curved and slightly right-sloping letters. A few letters
                        appear more angular, e.g., መ
                        ዐ.</note>
                     <note> Some peculiar features:
                        </note>
                     <note> - ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on
                        the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., <locus target="#19vb">19vb</locus>
                        l.22);</note>
                     <note> - ሎ has sometimes the 7th order marker
                        attached directly at the body of the letter, without horizontal stroke
                        (e.g., <locus target="#14ra">14ra</locus> l.8);
                        </note>
                     <note> - መ has the upper horizontal stroke,
                        in the 1st and in the 2nd orders, slightly slanted to the left; besides, the
                        right loop does not rest on the ruled
                        line;</note>
                     <note> - ኴ has the loop marking the 5th order
                        open (e.g., <locus target="#25ra">25ra</locus> l.30);
                        </note>
                     <note> - ፬ is triangular and down
                        wards-oriented (e.g., <locus target="#11ra">11ra</locus> l.20);
                        </note>
                     <note> - ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                        like “compressed” ፯ (e.g., <locus target="#84vb">84vb</locus>
                        l.22);</note>
                     <note> - ፪ has angular and not separated
                        loops (e.g., <locus target="#18ra">18ra</locus>
                        l.15).</note>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: coloured
                        (red, yellow, black), horizontal and vertical ornamental band, framing all
                        the text, above, around both lateral sides, between the two columns, below
                        the text. Geometric motifs (interlaces).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">- <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>: simple,
                        narrow, uncoloured (red), horizontal band (within the columns ab) dividing
                        two different texts. Geometric motifs (interlaces).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#73va">f. 73va</locus>
                           <desc type="CalendaricNote">Note concerning a church feast (?)</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#37va">37va</locus> (below the text): ዘገነተ፡ ማርያም፡ ግበሮ፡
                              ተስከ፡ ደቅቀ፡ በኀምሊ[sic]፡ አ፲ወ፸፨ ዘይኮን</q>
                           
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#118vb">f. 118vb</locus>
                           <desc type="Unclear">Unclear note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#118vb">118vb</locus> (below the text): በጠጁን፡ ከረዙን፡
                              እኑሆን፯፯፡ [n.l.]በል፡ ምዕደንግያ፡ ወሚመ፡ በዘ፡ ትትከል፡ ዕዕ፡ ዘኢያንቀበቅል፡ ድማም፡</q>
                           
                           <note> Crudely written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A few times, part of the lines (usually the last letter
                           of a word) from the incipit of the texts are written at the margin,
                           outside the column: e.g., <locus target="#39va">39va</locus>, 48vb, 79vb,
                           60ra.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">- Corrections over erasures: <locus target="#24ra">24ra</locus>, 31ra, 32vb, 38rb, 104va.
</item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"> - Erasures: fols. 36vb,
                           41ra.
</item>
                        <item xml:id="e3a"> - Cues for the rubricator (numbers) written in the margins of
                           the column: e.g., <locus target="#39v">39v</locus>, 59v.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">- Crude
                           notes in pen or in pencil on <locus target="#7v">7v</locus> (above the
                           text), 8v (above the text), 9r (above the text) and on the right inner
                           board.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Readings are indicated by the commemoration dates of
                              the Apostles, written in the main hand, in red or in black, in the
                              upper margin: አመ፲ለሐምሌ: ናትናኤል።: <locus target="#25r">fol. 25r</locus>
                              አመ፻ለጥር፡ ዮሐንስ።: <locus target="#28">fol. 28</locus>(a)r አመ፩ለመስከረም፡
                              በርተሎሜዎስ።: <locus target="#35r">fol. 35r</locus> አመ፳፪ለጥቅምት፡ ሉቃስ፡:
                                 <locus target="#39v">fol. 39v</locus> አመ፲፪ለጥቅምት፡ ማቴዎስ፡: <locus target="#41r">fol. 41r</locus> አመ፲ወ፰ለኀምሌ: ያዕቆብ።: fol 45v አመ፬ለታኅሣሥ:
                              አንድርያስ።: <locus target="#52v">fol. 52v</locus> አመ፡ ፲፰፡ ለኅደር፡: <locus target="#60ra">fol. 60ra</locus> አመ፲ለያ[sic]ካቲት፡ ያዕቆብ።: <locus target="#83r">fol. 83r</locus> አመ፰ለመጋቢት፡ ማቲያስ፡: <locus target="#84r">fol. 84r</locus> አመ፲ወ፯፡ ለሚያዝያ፡ ያዕቆብ።: <locus target="#93r">fol. 93r</locus> አመ፴ለሚያዝያ፡ ማርቆስ።: <locus target="#97v">fol. 97v</locus> አመ፳፮(?)፡ ለግንቦት፡ ቶማስ።: <locus target="#100v">fol. 100v</locus> አመ፪ለሐምሌ: ታዴዎስ።: <locus target="#114v">fol. 114v</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
